
[1]wafer

   WAFER, n.

   1. A thin cake or leaf; as a wafer of bread given by the Romanists in
   the Eucharist.

   2. A thin leaf of paste, or a composition of flour, the white of eggs,
   isinglass and yeast, spread over with gumwater and dried; used in
   sealing letters.

                 WAFER, v.t. To seal or close with a wafer.
